BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313278133@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T023931Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260315T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260315T170000
SUMMARY:History of Parkdale\, Sunnyside & Roncesvalles! (NEW FOR 2026)
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Yearl
 y Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tours\
 , email**\n**[torontohistorywalks@gmail.com](http://torontohistorywalks@gm
 ail.com/)**\n**for more information or for signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\* **Pl
 ease note: Please e-transfer the ticket amount when booking your space for
  this tour! You can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**[torontohis
 torywalks@gmail.com](http://torontohistorywalks@gmail.com/)**\n\nParkdale 
 has many faces.\n\nAnd over the years those faces have become sharper and 
 clearer to residents and visitors alike. The tone has changed in Parkdale.
  And that is always a good thing.\n\nOne of the main reasons why Toronto H
 istory Walks came into being was simply because the images of Parkdale at 
 the time\, 2019\, seemed to convey a negative picture of the neighbourhood
 . Toronto residents wanted to avoid Parkdale at all costs based on assumpt
 ions. It was dangerous and better to avoid than explore.\n\nBut those idea
 s have changed over the last several years. Parkdale is a great place to e
 xplore\, have a cup of coffee or dinner and check out the arts and enterta
 inment or take a stroll down a side street in one of the best preserved Vi
 ctorian neighbourhoods in Toronto.\n\nWelcome to Toronto's first suburb\, 
 the floral suburb. And it truly is a remarkable place to get to know. What
  Parkdale needed most was understanding. And this walk provides the intere
 sted walker with that understanding of how Parkdale came to be\, and why i
 t had a rather sketchy history right from its inception in 1879. And it ha
 d to do more with the attitudes of the residents than reality. Attitudes t
 hat followed the growth of Parkdale to this very day. Parkdale just can't 
 get free of its own legacy!\n\nFrom its beginnings in 1850 to the controve
 rsy surrounding the Gardiner Expressway\, and the death of Sunnyside Amuse
 ment Park\, the story of Parkdale unfolds\, and it has a remarkable abilit
 y to climb out of depressed economic periods. This is a detailed explorati
 on of the district.\n\nThis tour begins at the southwest corner of King\, 
 Queen\, and Roncesvalles\, at the Polish memorial Katyn\, just east of the
  Sunnyside pedestrian bridge across the street from the McDonald's.\n\nWe 
 wind our way through West Parkdale\, and end the tour at the TTC stop for 
 St. Joseph's Health Centre on the site of Sunnyside Villa!\n\nThis 2 hour 
 walking tour is for all walking levels. Please dress for the season\, and 
 hope to see you there.\n\nThis tour has a ticket price of $15.00 per perso
 n!\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticket amount when booki
 ng your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the following email at:
 **\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/events/313278
 133/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260209T125137Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260209T125137Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_312786410@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T023931Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260321T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260321T150000
SUMMARY:Lights\, Camera\, Action: Hollywood North Film Locations
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Explo
 rer Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tour
 s\, email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or 
 for signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the tic
 ket price when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the
  following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nMary Pickford
  stares into the camera.\n\nBorn on University Avenue\, she became the gir
 l with the golden curls\, the first Hollywood star\, and now Toronto is th
 e star!\n\nGood Will Hunting\, Pacific Rim\, X-Men\, Robocop\, Total Recal
 l\, Prom Night\, Suicide Squad\, My Big Fat Greek Wedding\, Police Academy
 \, and the list goes on and on and on.\n\nIt was back in the 1920s that To
 ronto emerged as a shy newcomer. But it stepped up to the camera\, smiled\
 , and went to work. The first real feature movie was "The Man From Toronto
 \," even though it was not filmed here\, and in the late 60s Toronto was "
 Goin' Down the Road\," that the city was Hollywood bound.\n\nAnd it wasn't
  just movies! Television movies\, series\, documentaries\, music videos an
 d video games were all shot here in Toronto. Award shows such as The Genie
 's\, Juno's\, the Canadian Screen Awards\, Giller Prize and The Much Music
  Video Awards are all celebrated here! Let's find out where the movies cam
 e alive with this unique walking tour!\n\nThis walking tour is for all wal
 king levels and fitness skills. Please dress for the season and bring wate
 r. And remember to bring your love of movie magic as well. Hope to see you
  there.\n\nThis tour begins at the famous TORONTO sign at Nathan Phillips 
 Square. We end at Front and Jarvis!\n\nThis tour has a ticket price of $15
 .00 per person!\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticket pric
 e when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the followi
 ng email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/events/312786
 410/
