CREATED:20260108T160516Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260108T160516Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313174345@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T023931Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260322T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260322T140000
SUMMARY:History of the Encyclopaedia Britannica (LECTURE ON THE GO)
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Explo
 rer Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tour
 s\, email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or 
 for signing up!\\*\\***\n\nWe have an amazing "Lecture on the Go" series f
 or 2026. New topics and fascinating stories abound! Join us and learn abou
 t the world and keep active and warm during the winter months!\n\nI starte
 d this walking classroom when we were under that horrible cloud called Cov
 id. This series was popular and helped people get out and back into societ
 y and life. The series is back for 2026 with 6 new topics for exploration 
 over the winter and spring months.\n\nThe "Lecture on the Go" Series is op
 en only to members who have purchased the YEARLY MEMBERSHIP PASS\, it's fr
 ee for those members. If you wish to attend a lecture and you are not a ye
 arly pass member then the price **per** lecture is $20.00.\n\nThis second 
 lecture is focussed on the search for world knowledge. In the mid 18th cen
 tury putting together a compendium of the world's knowledge was a monument
 al task. But it was done and it still around today. Let's uncover some of 
 the facts about this fascinating topic.\n\nEncyclopaedia Britannica got it
 s start in 1768 in Edinburgh\, when a group of very curious\, ambitious pe
 ople decided the world needed one big\, reliable place to put all knowledg
 e. This was the Enlightenment era\, so everyone was obsessed with reason\,
  learning\, and explaining things properly.\n\nThe early editions were bol
 d\, quirky\, and packed with everything from science and philosophy to pra
 ctical advice.\n\nBritannica grew into the champion of encyclopedias. It c
 rossed over to North America\, added volumes\, and became the go-to refere
 nce set in libraries\, schools\, and living rooms. Having a full set on yo
 ur shelf once meant you were serious about education—or at least wanted 
 to look that way. The articles were written by experts\, which gave Britan
 nica its reputation for authority\, even if some entries now feel dated.\n
 \nThen came the internet\, and everything changed. In 2012\, Britannica st
 opped printing its famous books and went digital\, trading leather for goo
 gle. Same mission as always—sharing trustworthy knowledge—just a lot l
 ighter to carry and easier to dust. And I have three full sets\, I should 
 know.\n\nTopics upcoming in the 2026 series of lectures are as follows. We
  are a little behind but catching up.\n\n\\*Dante\; The Hidden Meaning Beh
 ind The Divine Comedy\n\\*Hidden Wonders of Canada\; Northern Ontario Hist
 ory and Guide\n\\*Philosophy 1: Great Minds of the Western World: Goethe t
 o Kant!\n\\*Philosophy 2: Great Minds of the Eastern World: Chuang Tzu to 
 Dalai Lama\n\nHope to see you on this "Lecture on the Go!" So book your pl
 ans now!\n\nThis event is for all levels and walkers\, there are a few ste
 ps here and there to navigate\, but mostly on one level. This event in a n
 on walking event.\n\nThe lecture begins on the steps of Old City Hall at t
 he northeast corner of Bay Street and Queen Street West and head into the 
 PATH.\n\nThis lecture event has a ticket price of $20.00 per person\, and 
 is **free with the yearly membership pass**. Hope to see you there!\n\n\\*
 \\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticket amount when booking your s
 pace for this tour! You can e-transfer to the following email at:**\n**tor
 ontohistorywalks@gmail.com**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-history-of-parkdale/events/313174
 345/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260202T163159Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260202T163159Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
