SUMMARY:Historic Buildings Walking Tour!
DESCRIPTION:Toronto History Walks\n\\*\\***The Toronto History Walks Explo
 rer Pass is available. Get it now for $125.00 for 1 year of unlimited tour
 s\, email**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n**for more information or 
 for signing up!\\*\\***\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the tic
 ket amount when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to th
 e following email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**\n\nToronto has 
 a rich history\, and it's all around us\, but certain buildings do stand o
 ut and tell our story. On this walking tour the following buildings are ex
 plored and their history revealed. This new tour is for residents and tour
 ists who want to reconnect with their city\, or get to know it from a diff
 erent vantage point!\n\n* Daniel Brooke Building\n* St. Lawrence Hall\n* S
 t. James Anglican Cathedral\n* St. Michael's Cathedral\n* Mackenzie House\
 n* Massey Hall\n* Old City Hall\n* Osgoode Hall\n* Campbell House Museum\n
 * Gooderham Building\n\nand a few other hidden surprises along the way fro
 m the Toronto Stock Exchange to the New City Hall and a few others in betw
 een!\n\nThis walking tour is for all walking levels. Please dress for the 
 season\, and hope to see you there.\n\nPlease meet in front of the iconic 
 St. Lawrence Hall at the corner of Jarvis and King Street East\, we end th
 e tour at Historic Campbell House!\n\nThis tour has a ticket price of $15.
 00 per person.\n\n\\*\\* **Please note: Please e-transfer the ticket amoun
 t when booking your space for this tour! You can e-transfer to the followi
 ng email at:**\n**torontohistorywalks@gmail.com**
